<exercise checkit-seed="0022" checkit-slug="E1" checkit-title="Linear systems, vector equations, and augmented matrices">
  <statement>
    <p>Consider the vector equation.</p>
    <me> x_{1} \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \\
-4 \\
-2 \\
0
\end{array}\right] + x_{2} \left[\begin{array}{c}
-2 \\
5 \\
1 \\
3
\end{array}\right] + x_{3} \left[\begin{array}{c}
5 \\
-1 \\
-4 \\
8
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{c}
2 \\
-5 \\
-1 \\
-3
\end{array}\right] </me>
    <ol>
      <li> Write a system of scalar equations corresponding to this vector equation. </li>
      <li> Write an augmented matrix corresponding to this vector equation. </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <md alignment="alignat" alignat-columns=" 4 ">
          <mrow>3 \, x_{1} &amp;-&amp; 2 \, x_{2} &amp;+&amp; 5 \, x_{3} &amp;=&amp; 2</mrow>
          <mrow>-4 \, x_{1} &amp;+&amp; 5 \, x_{2} &amp;-&amp; x_{3} &amp;=&amp; -5</mrow>
          <mrow>-2 \, x_{1} &amp;+&amp; x_{2} &amp;-&amp; 4 \, x_{3} &amp;=&amp; -1</mrow>
          <mrow> &amp; &amp; 3 \, x_{2} &amp;+&amp; 8 \, x_{3} &amp;=&amp; -3</mrow>
        </md>
      </li>
      <li>
        <me> \left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
3 &amp; -2 &amp; 5 &amp; 2 \\
-4 &amp; 5 &amp; -1 &amp; -5 \\
-2 &amp; 1 &amp; -4 &amp; -1 \\
0 &amp; 3 &amp; 8 &amp; -3
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

